about.summary: Proliantutils is a set of utility libraries for interfacing and managing various components (like iLO, HPSSA) for HP Proliant Servers. This library is used by iLO drivers in Ironic for managing Proliant Servers (though the library can be used by anyone who wants to manage HP Proliant servers).

name: proliantutils
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "proliantutils" %}
{% set version = "2.8.4" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 0a199b36b2daf81c70421c9a6c697c49c3dbcfe1e56bd270d8e6c1ef04456f40

build:
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed -vv "

requirements:
  host:
    - pbr >=2.0.0
    - pip
    - python
  run:
    - jsonschema !=2.5.0,<3.0.0,>=2.0.0
    - oslo.concurrency >=3.8.0
    - oslo.serialization >=1.10.0
    - oslo.utils >=3.20.0
    - pbr >=2.0.0
    - pysnmp >=4.2.3,<5.0.0
    - python
    - requests !=2.12.2,!=2.13.0,>=2.10.0
    - retrying !=1.3.0,>=1.2.3
    - six >=1.9.0
    - sushy >=1.8.0

test:
  imports:
    - proliantutils
    - proliantutils.exception
    - proliantutils.log
    - proliantutils.utils

about:
  home: https://github.com/openstack/proliantutils
  license: Apache Software
  license_family: APACHE
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Proliantutils is a set of utility libraries for interfacing and managing various components (like iLO, HPSSA) for HP Proliant Servers. This library is used by iLO drivers in Ironic for managing Proliant Servers (though the library can be used by anyone who wants to manage HP Proliant servers).

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - pg-hbk
    - sy-hbk
